content.description: Starfish Right is a bit harder than its neighbor. Stand start with a left hand on the arete and a right hand on a good face hold. Work up the arete until you can get your left foot on it to round over to the face, and top out on easier terrain.
content.location: Find the arete to the left of Raging Panda.

content.description: Sit start on the offwidth, make moves up, and traverse left on the lip with bad foot holds until you find a shelve to top out.
content.location: This is located on a small alcove in the middle of Patrick's House. Look for left-leaning arete which is about 5 feet high.

content.description: Sit start on the left side of the arete with your right hand on the arete and your left hand on a good face jug. Pull up onto the face, and work your way up the arete. A couple of options will allow you to complete the rest of the climb.
content.location: Find the obvious arete to the left of Raging Panda.

content.description: Climb the chimney. Don't crawl to the back, just climb up it and out. This is good practice for suffering in small chimneys.
content.location: It is on the right side of the crag.

content.description: Patrick's House is a small cliff (or is it a pile of boulders?) near the northwest tip of Walden Pond. Check out the photos.
